entry.def: If a liquid is diluted or dilutes, it is added to or mixes with water or another liquid, and becomes weaker.

example.ex: If you give your baby juice, dilute it well with cooled, boiled water...
example.tran: 如果给婴儿喝果汁，要用凉开水充分稀释。

entry.def: A dilute liquid is very thin and weak, usually because it has had water added to it.
If someone or something dilutes a belief, quality, or value, they make it weaker and less effective.

example.ex: There was a clear intention to dilute black voting power...
example.tran: 明显有意图要削弱黑人的选举力量。

example.ex: Serious attention is being given to diluting the value of personal tax allowances.
example.tran: 人们正密切关注降低个人收入免税额度一事。

means.word_mean: 1. reduced in strength or concentration or quality or purity;
